TensorFlow is an open-source software library for dataflow programming across a range of tasks. It is a symbolic math library, and 
also used for machine learning applications such as neural networks. It is used for both research and production at Google, often 
replacing its closed-source predecessor, DistBelief.

TensorFlow was developed by the Google Brain team for internal Google use. It was released under the Apache 2.0 open source license 
on November 9, 2015.

To install Tensorflow on ubuntu, we do some steps:
Step 1: Dowload and install anaconda
Dowload: https://www.anaconda.com/download/#linux
Install:
$ bash Anaconda3-5.0.1-Linux-x86_64.sh
$ conda create -n tensorflow python=3.6

Step 2: Use tensorflow
acer@aspire:~$ source activate tensorflow
(tensorflow) acer@aspire:~$ spyder

Step 3: Enjoy


Windows:
1) Cài đặt Anaconda
Link: https://www.anaconda.com/download/
2) Cài đặt tensorflow
Click phải Anaconda Prompt chọn Run Administrator
(base) C:\WINDOWS\system32>conda create -n tensorflow python=3.6
(base) C:\WINDOWS\system32>activate tensorflow
(tensorflow) C:\WINDOWS\system32>spyder
3) Update IDE và thu viện
(base) C:\WINDOWS\system32>conda update conda
(base) C:\WINDOWS\system32>conda update anaconda
(base) C:\WINDOWS\system32>conda update spyder
(base) C:\WINDOWS\system32>conda update --all
(base) C:\WINDOWS\system32>conda update -n base conda
4) Install keras
(tensorflow) C:\WINDOWS\system32>conda install -c conda-forge keras 
5) Install statsmodels
(tensorflow) C:\WINDOWS\system32>conda install -c conda-forge statsmodels
6) Install deap (thư viện genetic algorithms)
(tensorflow) C:\WINDOWS\system32>conda install -c conda-forge deap 